---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Section from '../../components/Section.astro';
import Button from '../../components/Button.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Platform Technical Audit"
  description="130+ structural checks across server, platform, and template tiers. Sprint-ready dev backlog with code fixes, every finding tagged with severity, root cause cluster, and confidence tier."
>
  <Section class="pt-28 pb-16">
    <div class="max-w-3xl">
      <p class="text-accent font-mono text-sm mb-4">The Get Right &rsaquo; Platform Technical Audit</p>
      <h1 class="mb-6">Platform Technical Audit</h1>
      <p class="text-accent text-lg font-medium mb-4">Powered by Muttr</p>
      <p class="text-secondary-text text-xl leading-relaxed">
        130+ structural checks across three tiers &mdash; server, platform, and template.
        Every finding tagged with severity, root cause cluster, and confidence tier.
        Delivered as sprint-ready tickets with code fixes, not a PDF of suggestions.
      </p>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section elevated>
    <h2 class="mb-8">What we examine</h2>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
      <div class="bg-bg-surface border border-border-subtle rounded-lg p-6">
        <h4 class="text-accent mb-3">Server Tier</h4>
        <ul class="text-secondary-text space-y-1.5 text-base">
          <li>TLS configuration and certificate chain</li>
          <li>HTTP/2+ support and protocol negotiation</li>
          <li>Security headers (CSP, HSTS, X-Frame-Options)</li>
          <li>CDN configuration and caching strategy</li>
          <li>TTFB and server response optimization</li>
          <li>Redirect chain analysis</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-bg-surface border border-border-subtle rounded-lg p-6">
        <h4 class="text-accent mb-3">Platform Tier</h4>
        <ul class="text-secondary-text space-y-1.5 text-base">
          <li>CMS/framework detection and version analysis</li>
          <li>Core Web Vitals (LCP, INP, CLS) with root causes</li>
          <li>Resource loading and render-blocking audit</li>
          <li>Third-party script impact analysis</li>
          <li>Consent management and privacy compliance</li>
          <li>Ad stack conflicts and duplicate tags</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-bg-surface border border-border-subtle rounded-lg p-6">
        <h4 class="text-accent mb-3">Template Tier</h4>
        <ul class="text-secondary-text space-y-1.5 text-base">
          <li>Structured data validation and completeness</li>
          <li>Image optimization (format, sizing, lazy loading)</li>
          <li>Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA compliance)</li>
          <li>Mobile responsiveness and viewport issues</li>
          <li>Internal linking structure</li>
          <li>Form friction and UX patterns</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-bg-surface border border-border-subtle rounded-lg p-6">
        <h4 class="text-accent mb-3">Root Cause Synthesis</h4>
        <ul class="text-secondary-text space-y-1.5 text-base">
          <li>Pattern detection across findings</li>
          <li>Systemic vs. one-off issue classification</li>
          <li>Compliance risk flagging (GDPR, CCPA, WCAG)</li>
          <li>Confidence tier per finding (confirmed / probable / hypothesis)</li>
          <li>Fix prioritization by severity &times; effort</li>
          <li>Dependency chain mapping</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section>
    <h2 class="mb-8">The deliverable</h2>
    <div class="max-w-2xl">
      <p class="text-secondary-text text-lg mb-6">
        Not a report. A backlog. Every finding ships as a markdown file with a
        machine-readable YAML masthead and a rendered human-readable body &mdash;
        ready to drop into your engineering tracker.
      </p>
      <div class="bg-bg-inset border border-border-subtle rounded-lg p-6 font-mono text-sm overflow-x-auto">
        <!-- YAML frontmatter -->
        <div class="text-secondary-text">---</div>
        <div><span class="text-secondary-text">finding_id:</span> <span class="text-accent">"perf-014"</span></div>
        <div><span class="text-secondary-text">title:</span> <span class="text-primary-text">"Render-blocking CSS on mobile"</span></div>
        <div><span class="text-secondary-text">severity:</span> <span class="text-danger">"high"</span></div>
        <div><span class="text-secondary-text">root_cause_cluster:</span> <span class="text-warning">"Unoptimized Web Font Loading"</span></div>
        <div class="break-words"><span class="text-secondary-text">why_this_matters:</span> <span class="text-primary-text">"Mobile LCP exceeds 4s on first visit, failing Core Web Vitals and degrading first-impression experience for half of inbound traffic."</span></div>
        <div class="break-words"><span class="text-secondary-text">fix_summary:</span> <span class="text-primary-text">"Preload critical font faces; defer non-critical with font-display: swap."</span></div>
        <div><span class="text-secondary-text">confidence_tier:</span> <span class="text-success">"confirmed"</span></div>
        <div class="text-secondary-text mb-4">---</div>

        <!-- Rendered body -->
        <div class="text-primary-text font-heading text-base mb-3">Render-blocking CSS on mobile</div>
        <div class="text-secondary-text mb-1.5"><span class="text-primary-text font-semibold">Finding:</span> Render-blocking CSS on mobile</div>
        <div class="text-secondary-text mb-1.5"><span class="text-primary-text font-semibold">Severity:</span> High</div>
        <div class="text-secondary-text mb-1.5"><span class="text-primary-text font-semibold">Why this matters:</span> Mobile LCP exceeds 4s on first visit, failing Core Web Vitals.</div>
        <div class="text-secondary-text mb-1.5"><span class="text-primary-text font-semibold">Root cause:</span> Unoptimized Web Font Loading</div>
        <div class="text-secondary-text"><span class="text-primary-text font-semibold">Fix:</span> Preload critical font faces; defer non-critical with font-display: swap.</div>
      </div>
      <p class="text-secondary-text text-sm mt-4">
        Every finding follows this format. The YAML masthead is for indexing
        &mdash; finding ID, severity, root cause cluster, confidence tier. The
        body is the readable explanation and fix. Both ship in one file.
      </p>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section elevated>
    <div class="max-w-2xl">
      <h2 class="mb-4">How it connects</h2>
      <p class="text-secondary-text text-lg mb-6">
        Technical findings feed directly into the other two pillars. Slow page speed
        becomes a conversion cost in the Revenue Performance Audit. Missing structured
        data becomes a content visibility gap in the Content Authority Audit.
      </p>
      <p class="text-secondary-text text-lg">
        That cross-pollination is why a single-pillar audit misses things.
        A technical issue isn't just a technical issue &mdash; it's a revenue issue.
      </p>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section>
    <div class="text-center">
      <h2 class="mb-4">See it in action</h2>
      <p class="text-secondary-text text-lg mb-8 max-w-xl mx-auto">
        See how the Platform Technical Audit fits into the full Get Right
        engagement &mdash; or talk to a founder about your site.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-4">
        <Button href="/the-get-right">See The Full Get Right</Button>
        <Button href="/contact" variant="secondary">Talk to a Founder</Button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Section>
</BaseLayout>
